            <bug_when>2009-10-02 08:08:04 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>The current implementation of the data binding controllers always uses qx.util.PropertyUtil.getProperties to check for the availability of the accessed properties. But this function only returns the properties of the given class and not of its superclasses. So if a necessary property is defined by a superclass, the binding will fail.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
